oggfwd:
A basic icecast client that is very simple but also very useful for video streaming :-)
It has some metadata information not included in the original oggfwd. 

Dependencies:
- libshout >= 2.1 
- libogg
- libvorbis
- libtheora

Homepage:
 http://www.v2v.cc/~j/ffmpeg2theora/oggfwd

Basic help:

================
...|> Simple Usage: 
 oggfwd server_address port_number password target
Sample:
 oggfwd icecast.v2v.cc 8000 password /theora.ogg

...|> Advanced Usage:
Use strings (a single word or a "w o r d" with spaces, inside " " ) or use the
possible values available inside the parentheses: -> 0 means False | 1 means True <-

Command Format:
 oggfwd server_address port_number password mount_point radio_name url genre description set_public(0,1) dump_file(0,dump_file_name) 

Sample:
 oggfwd orelhao.radiolivre.org 8100 secret_password /mount_point.ogg "Radio Freak" http://doidos.radiolivre.org/ free_style "A Radio dos doid@s" 1 /tmp/dumpfile.ogg 
================

